org.nzdis.micro

Class DefaultCljSocialRole

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nzdis.micro.AbstractRole
      • org.nzdis.micro.DefaultSocialRole
        • org.nzdis.micro.DefaultCljSocialRole
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Role, SocialRole

    public abstract class DefaultCljSocialRole
extends DefaultSocialRole
    The DefaultCljSocialRole is a specialization of the DefaultSocialRole and assumes that message handling is done in Clojure. It expects a Clojure script in the application or role script folder on instantiation. This must include the function "receive-msg [message]" being able to handle incoming MicroMessages. Given this, no Java code will need to written for agent implementation as sending can be accomplished using the function (send-msg ) in Clojure. See commonAgentBase.clj for alternative message sending functions.
